## 7. Mitigation and Enhancement Measures

- **Air Emissions:**
    - Preventive maintenance; anti-idling policy; low-sulfur diesel where available; explore electrification/retrofits; dust control on unpaved areas; driver/operator training.
- **Noise:**
    - Mufflers/maintenance; schedule noisy activities daytime; acoustic enclosures for generators; PPE for workers; quarterly monitoring at boundary.
- **Water/Soils:**
    - Bunded storage; drip trays; oil-water separators; housekeeping; spill booms on drains during refueling/maintenance; no direct discharge of untreated effluents.
- **Spill Prevention/Response:**
    - SPCC plan; spill kits and booms at high-risk points; trained ERT with drills; NOSDRA notification protocol; maintain inventory and inspection logs.
- **Waste Management:**
    - Segregation at source; labeled containers; licensed waste haulers; manifests; no open burning; promote recycling where feasible.
- **Biodiversity:**
    - No in-water works; strict spill prevention; waste control; awareness training; prohibit wildlife disturbance.
- **Traffic/Navigation:**
    - Traffic management plan; signage and speed limits; segregation of pedestrian and vehicle paths; competent drivers/operators; marine movements coordinated with NPA/NIMASA.
- **OHS and Women-Led Safety:**
    - Implement ISO 45001-aligned OHS system; P2W for high-risk tasks; JSA; LOTO; WAH rescue plans; shift-level female HSE Champions; stop-work authority.
- **Social/Community:**
    - Stakeholder engagement, community safety information, grievance mechanism, local hiring and training; enforce anti-harassment and GBV/SEA protocols with confidential reporting.
- **Climate/Resilience:**
    - Energy efficiency; LED lighting; GHG accounting; drainage improvements; severe weather preparedness and drills.

